summary: I am a passionate environmentalist who has a background in ecology and geoscience. I recently began a new role as a geographical surveyor at Deep bv in which I am learning a whole host of new skills and knowledge. Conducting field surveys and processing data. I have a specific interest in archeological projects. Outside of this, I enjoy hiking, yoga and bouldering. In 2022 I completed my Masters Earth Science: Future Planet Ecosystem Science at The University of Amsterdam. During my studies I gained invaluable skills in report writing, conducting research projects from start to finish and publishing work. In June 2020 I graduated with 2:1 in BSc Geography-Geoscience from the University of Aberdeen.
